"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167102","Home Office","false","2014-12-15","<p>Those looking to work in the UK use Tiers 2 and 5 of the Points Based System route. A list of Certificates of Sponsorship (CoS) assigned by sponsors, by business <br>sector, has been placed in the Library of the House. This list provides details of the certificates that have been assigned and will not necessarily have leave granted in conjunction with that CoS.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-12-15T12:22:45.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167102/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167102/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167102/answer/previousversion/31675","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-01","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information her Department holds on the professions of non-EU migrants who have entered the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","216718"
