"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166707","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>The dates for Initial Gate and, where completed, Main Gate and contract signature for each of the programmes and projects listed are provided in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>The contract signature date has been taken to refer to a post-Main Gate manufacture phase contract. Contract signature dates for any contracts let earlier in the Concept, Assessment, Development, Manufacturing, In-Service and Disposal (CADMID) cycle, such as those for Assessment or Demonstration phases, or contracts let for Long Lead items, have not been included. However, for those programmes where the information requested is not complete, a note on their current status has been provided.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","216428 ; 216429 ; 216438","2014-12-05T13:36:01.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166707/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166707/answer","Programme Initial Gate and contract Signature Dates.doc","Programme Initial Gate and contract Signature Dates.doc","Programmes and Projects Lists ","Programmes and Projects Lists ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166707/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the date was of (a) initial gate, (b) main gate and (c) contract signature was for the (i) A400M Training Service, (ii) Airseeker, (iii) Brimstone 2, (iv) Beyond Visual Range Air to Air Missile on Lightning II, (v) Common Missile Compartment, (vi) Core Production Capability, (vii) Crypto Enabling Services and (viii) De-Equip, Defuel and Layup Preparations Facility projects.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","216426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166708","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>A total of 36 interpreters have been relocated to the UK with 19 family members during the past four months as part of the ex-gratia redundancy scheme. The relocation programme requires appropriate identity, health, medical and security checks for the individual and any immediate family. We expect the pace of relocations to increase significantly in the New Year.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-05T13:34:52.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166708/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166708/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many locally-employed Afghan interpreters who worked alongside the British Army have resettled to the UK under his Department's resettlement package.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","216471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166709","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"> </td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>Of the 321 Afghan patrol interpreters who worked alongside UK forces between November 2013 and October 2014, 237 no longer work with us. Of these, 218 have applied for UK relocation.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-05T13:33:41.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166709/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166709/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many locally-employed Afghan patrol interpreters who worked alongside the British Army between November 2013 and October 2014 have applied for resettlement in the UK.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","216472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166710","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>Of the 321 Afghan patrol interpreters who worked alongside UK forces between November 2013 and October 2014, 237 no longer work with us. Of these, 228 are eligible for relocation to the UK. 84 are still working for us and their eligibility will be confirmed at the point of redundancy.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-05T13:34:20.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166710/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166710/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many locally-employed Afghan patrol interpreters who worked alongside the British Army between November 2013 and October 2014 are eligible to apply for resettlement in UK.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","216473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166711","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-04","<p>As the previous Defence Secretary, my right hon. Friend Mr Hammond stated on 14 January 2014 (Official Report, column 717) the additional costs of the interim IT solution is around £1 million per month. The current cost to date is around £9 million.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-12-04T15:58:21.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166711/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166711/answer","14 Jan 2014.doc It systems (Army ).doc","14 Jan 2014.doc It systems (Army ).doc","Hansard Extract IT systems (Army Recruitment)","Hansard Extract IT systems (Army Recruitment)","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166711/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent to date on the running costs of the interim IT solution put in place while Capita develop a new platform for the management of regular and reserve soldier recruitment.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166712","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>Construction of the Capita ICT platform was originally due for completion in February 2015, to be followed by testing and transfer of data prior to going live. Capita remain committed to delivering the new enhanced recruiting website by July 2015 as part of the new ICT Platform.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-12-05T14:15:41.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166712/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166712/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department is on schedule to introduce the advanced IT system developed in partnership with Capita to manage the recruitment of regular and reserve soldiers by February 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166713","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>The numbers of security incidents recorded centrally within the Ministry of Defence (MOD) in each of the years in question is set out in the table below. The figures relate to incidents in which information has not been fully protected, including lost documents, missing computer media and possible unauthorised access to classified information. These figures also include incidents which represented a failure of a control but did not result in the loss of any information.</p><p> </p><p>The vast majority of incidents did not have any significant ramifications for Defence security. The apparent increase in incidents is attributed to a progressively increasing readiness to report even minor breaches, not to systematic failings in security protection.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table Number of Information Security Incidents by Year</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>885</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>893</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>920</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>1,194</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The MOD treats all breaches of security very seriously. All reported breaches are subjected to an initial security risk assessment with further action taken on a proportionate basis. We do not maintain central records of the specific action taken following each of the breaches.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-12-05T13:52:55.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166713/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166713/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many security breaches have been recorded by the Ministry of Defence in each year since 2010; and what action has been taken following each such breach.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166714","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-04","<p>Guidance on the raising of the recruitment age to 50 years old for those with specialist skills to become Officers in the Army Reserve was given in an Army Briefing Note published in May 2012. This was further published as part of a Defence Instruction and Notice issued in August 2014.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-12-04T16:14:59.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166714/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166714/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what guidance the armed forces have given his Department on the raising of the upper age limit of recruitment of those with specialist skills to become Officers in the Army Reserve from 45 to 50 years old.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166715","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-04","<p>Expenditure on redundancy payments is not recorded separately by the single Services. However, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) does record the total expenditure incurred by civilian and Armed Forces redundancy payments collectively. These are reported each year in the MOD's Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p>We do not gather details of the average redundancy payment.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-12-04T16:13:07.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166715/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166715/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-28","Armed Forces: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make it his policy to gather figures on the total and average sum paid out in redundancy packages for each branch of the armed services (a) since 2010 and (b) in future years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166716","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education does not collect information regarding the number of home-schooled children in England.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:19:14.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166716/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166716/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of home-educated children in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166717","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education does not collect information regarding the attainment of home-schooled children in England. Education in Wales is a devolved matter.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:44:29.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166717/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166717/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of the educational attainment of children who are home-educated in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166718","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p><br>The Department for Education officials have met with the policy committee of the Association of Directors of Children’s Services; officers of Darlington Borough Council; the children’s services scrutiny committee of the City of Westminster, and two regional forums of local authority elective home education officers; one for London and the South East and the other for the West Midlands.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:47:31.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166718/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166718/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 24 November 2014 to Question 214684, which representative bodies she or representatives of her Department have met in autumn 2014 to discuss home schooling and safeguarding.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166719","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education has made no such assessment. The identification of children not receiving a suitable education, and those within that number at risk for safeguarding reasons, is a matter for each local authority.</p><p> </p><p>Home education in Wales is a matter for the Welsh Government.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:21:06.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166719/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166719/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166719/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department's Independent Education and School Governance Division has made of the number of homeschooled children in England and Wales (a) in total and (b) who are believed to be at risk in relation to safeguarding.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166720","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education does not keep records in the form requested.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","216347 ; 216348","2014-12-04T18:30:40.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166720/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166720/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many homeschooling safeguarding concerns were raised by local authorities with her Department's Independent Education and School Governance Division in (a) 2012, (b) 2013 and (c) 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166721","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education does not keep records in the form requested.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","216346 ; 216348","2014-12-04T18:30:40.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166721/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166721/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166721/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which local authorities raised safeguarding matters relating to homeschooled children with her Department in (a) 2012, (b) 2013 and (c) 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166722","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education does not keep records in the form requested.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","216346 ; 216347","2014-12-04T18:30:40.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166722/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166722/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which local authorities raised education matters relating to homeschooled children with her Department in (a) 2012, (b) 2013 and (c) 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166723","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>If a child of compulsory school age is being educated at home but is not receiving a full-time education as required by section 7 of the Education Act 1996, the appropriate remedy is not prosecution but the serving of a school attendance order. If the parent does not comply with such an order, prosecution may then follow.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:34:26.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166723/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166723/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166723/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many parents were (a) investigated and (b) prosecuted for failing to ensure that their children were receiving insufficient hours of education whilst being homeschooled in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166724","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>The Department for Education does not collect data regarding local investigations of parents who fail to ensure their school registered children attend school regularly.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice Court Proceedings Database holds information on defendants proceeded against, found guilty and sentenced for criminal offences in England and Wales and it is published online at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-statistics-quarterly-december-2013" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-statistics-quarterly-december-2013</a></p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice has provided the information you requested in the attached spreadsheet.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:28:08.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166724/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166724/answer","Defendants_for_truancy_offences_2009-13.xls","Defendants_for_truancy_offences_2009-13.xls","Defendants for truancy offences 2009-13","Defendants for truancy offences 2009-13","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166724/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Truancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many parents were (a) investigated and (b) prosecuted for failing to ensure that their children attended school on a sufficiently regular basis in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166725","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Answer I gave him on 24 November (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-11-17/214706/" target="_blank">214706</a>) in relation to an estimate of the number of children missing from education in England and Wales.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education does not produce an assessment of the reasons for those children missing education. Education in Wales is a devolved matter.The Welsh Government is responsible for polices and legislation regarding children missing from education in Wales.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:36:52.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166725/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166725/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166725/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Education: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department produces an annual (a) estimate of the number of children missing from education in England and Wales and (b) assessment of the reasons for those children being missing.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166726","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>At present, as I indicated in the Answer I gave to the hon. Member on 20 October (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-10-14/210289/" target="_blank">210289</a>), we are discussing with local authorities the concerns they have about information available on children who are educated at home. We have not yet reached any conclusion as to whether any changes are needed to the Department’s guidance document or the current framework within which home education operates.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","216354","2014-12-04T18:39:58.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166726/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166726/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166726/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will bring forward proposals to require all parents who are engaged in homeschooling to register their child with the local authority for safeguarding purposes irrespective of whether the child has ever attended full-time in-school education.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166727","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>Section 7 of the Education Act 1996 already places a duty on the parent of every child of compulsory school age to ensure the child receives a full-time education suitable to the child’s age, ability, aptitude and any special education needs the child may have either by regular attendance at school or by education otherwise, for example, home education.</p><p> </p><p>In addition the law places a duty on local authorities to make arrangements to identify, as far as it is possible, children of compulsory school age in their area who are not registered pupils at a school and are not receiving suitable education otherwise than at school. It is the duty of the local authority to ensure those children are identified and receive a suitable full-time education.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2014-12-04T18:42:36.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166727/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166727/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166727/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Education: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will bring forward proposals to require all parents to ensure that their children are in full-time education irrespective of whether this is delivered in the home or in a school.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166728","Department for Education","false","2014-12-04","<p>At present, as I indicated in the Answer I gave to the hon. Member on 20 October (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-10-14/210289/" target="_blank">210289</a>), we are discussing with local authorities the concerns they have about information available on children who are educated at home. We have not yet reached any conclusion as to whether any changes are needed to the Department’s guidance document or the current framework within which home education operates.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb","216352","2014-12-04T18:39:58.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166728/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166728/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will bring forward proposals to require local authorities to register children who are homeschooled.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","216354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166729","Department for Education","false","2014-12-03","<p>The East Ham Police Station site is currently earmarked for the London Design and Engineering (LDE) University Technical College (UTC). However, the Department for Education has not yet entered into a funding agreement with the LDE UTC trust and is in discussion with the trust about the development of the project, including the most suitable site to meet the UTC’s needs. A number of other new school projects are also currently being considered as alternative options for the East Ham Police Station site. A decision will be made in early 2015.</p><p> </p><p>Given the sensitivity of the discussions I am not able to to release the names of the projects at this stage.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-12-03T17:32:46.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166729/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166729/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Schools: East Ham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what new school projects are currently being considered for the East Ham Police Station site which has recently been acquired by the Education Funding Agency; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166730","Department for Education","false","2014-12-03","<p>The information is not available in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>Information on teacher retention is currently derived from the Database of Teacher Records (DTR). However, this data source does not contain information on either the subject(s) of a teacher’s qualifications or the subject taught by the teacher.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-12-03T16:51:58.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166730/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166730/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the retention rate is for secondary school teachers of each subject area.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","216419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166731","Department for Education","false","2014-12-03","<p>The UK Government believes that strong and effective laws already exist in the UK under which individuals, including children, may seek enforceable remedies in the courts or tribunals if they feel that their rights have been breached. We do not therefore currently believe that ratification of the Optional Protocol is necessary. Nonetheless, the Government will continue to keep this under review.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-12-03T17:01:45.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166731/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166731/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-28","UN Convention on the Rights of the Child","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will bring forward legislative proposals to enable the ratification of the Optional Protocol to the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child on a communications procedure.","false","Biography information for Annette Brooke","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Annette Brooke","216416"
